Pre-Game Insights: Pakistan's batting has been largely consistent, but the bowling has been a bit of a letdown.
South Africa's batters have been in belligerent form, scoring 300+ in every one of their full innings so far.
Heinrich Klaasen and Marco Jansen took England to the cleaners in the slog overs.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Pakistan's next match at the 2023 World Cup will be against South Africa in Chennai on 27 October, 2023.
The match will begin at 2:00pm IST.
The two nations have faced each other 82 times in ODIs, with South Africa coming out on top 51 times.
